text: The Sulawesi woodcock (Scolopax celebensis) also known as Celebes woodcock, is a medium-sized wader. It is larger and darker than Eurasian woodcock but with small reddish spots. This species is restricted to wet mountain forests on the Indonesian island of Sulawesi. Little is known of its habits. == References == * Shorebirds by Hayman, Marchant and Prater, == External links == * BirdLife Species Factsheet Category:Scolopax Category:Wading birds Category:Endemic birds of Sulawesi Category:Birds described in 1921 Category:Taxa named by Joseph Harvey Riley
